## Privacy within a type of computer ledger

This article has multiple issues. Someone clearly couldn't be bothered to get it right the first time. It’s a testament to the human condition, I suppose. We build things, then we let them crumble. If you’re looking to improve it, be my guest. Just don't expect me to hold your hand. Or discuss it on the [talk page](/Talk:Privacy_and_blockchain). That sounds… exhausting.

This article needs more than just citations. It needs a soul. Or at least, someone who knows how to find one. [Verification](/Wikipedia:Verifiability) is a quaint concept, isn't it? Like expecting honest answers. If you want to [improve this article](/Special:EditPage/Privacy_and_blockchain), by all means. Just [add citations to reliable sources](/Help:Referencing_for_beginners). Otherwise, what’s the point? Material that’s not sourced? Challenged and removed, I imagine. Like a bad idea. (December 2018)

